ame, but have watched my friend play for years, decided to give it a go myself.  I have 2 computers, so run a cleric and a war at the same time.  <br>
<br>
My friend was excited that I decided to play, so gave me an early cristmas present, some cash to give my chara's some better gear, lol.  <br>
<br>
Just wanted to ask if what I got was decent?  The advice of my elders, I guess, is what I'm asking for.   I took the advice from other peoples posts, and their questions, and just wanted to know if the total package, that is now on my war, was worth the 8k or so that I was given.  I got about 20 in totall from my friend, spent about another 7k on the cleric, and have about 5k left.  <br>
<br>
Anything that I should get for my warrior that would be in that 5k pricerange?<br>
<br>
Thanks everyone in advance, for any advice that you give.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=494369"><br>
Avenol Whiteflame, 30 Warrior</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=534768">Rezzinx Shadowsoul, 30 Cleric of Tunare</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
The Rathe<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=akamekministud>akamek ministud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/25/02 10:21:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re: introduction, and a question</span><hr size=1> Well imo you are doing pretty good with the warrior.   If you only two box and rarely group you may like to find a nice two hander to try and up you dps.  A Tantor's Tusk could work great because there is no reco lvl and you can't really argue with a 50 dmg 60 dly +50hp and i think +10sv cold. They go for between 1500pp and 3500pp on Prexus from what I've seen recently.  Sure it's kinda slow but I like it for when I duo with my cousins druid lol, and those big crips are fun to see occasionally.  However if you group and lose aggro at times a Wrapped Entropy Serpent Spine is good for getting aggro just make sure after you proc you stay close to the mob or the blind spell will fear it.  The spine is something like 12 dmg 23 dly +12 ac and has some kinda blinding proc.  I think your armor is pretty nice, however if you forego the weapon upgrades some Barbed Ringmail couldn't hurt.  It's 30 ac +9 str and +50 hp and on Prexus is normally around 3kpp.  These are just random things that come to mind, so do what you want with my recomendations.  I hope I help and goodluck with your warrior.<br>
                          Akamek Ministud <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=knomekabobb>KnomeKabobb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/25/02 11:13:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re: introduction, and a question</span><hr size=1> I'd try to sell your Scimmy of Ethereal Energy and score on a Barbed Ringmail, a second Lamentation and a Hooded Black Cloak if you can.  I don't know about your server's prices though, so you might not be able to.<br>
<br>
Also, look into Electrum Black Sapphire Earrings if you have left over cash, 2ac 35hp from earring is nice, and shouldn't cost more than 200-300 a piece. <p>[55 Myrmidon]<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=475259">Bulky Behemoth</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->(Troll)<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.savagearms.org">&lt;Savage Arms&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jonnaspovar>Jonnas Povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/02 5:15:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Introduction, and a question.</span><hr size=1> Drop the lodi boots. Sell em and get cobalt, 11ac&gt;whatever else the boots give. Drop the hero bracer and get bracer of scavenging or crusty. I'd drop the neck slot and get a glimmering mithril torque. Drop the scimmy (they're pretty expensive on my server, for some reason) and pick up somethin like a jade mace, nother lammy, guard captain's mallet, or even a frosty depending on what they go for on your server. Or you could sell them both and get a nice 2hander....I'd also drop the cloak and get chetari shield, under 1k on povar and is a 12ac upgrade i believe. Just my 2cp (can't remember the rest of your stuff to comment on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69159"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/jonnaspovar/jonnas.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avenol>Avenol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/26/02 7:37:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Introduction, and a question.</span><hr size=1> Liked the suggestions, don't agree with the boots though, lemme try to figure it out a bit. <br>
<br>
Cobalt Boots<br>
25ac<br>
Effect: Strength of the Kunzar,  Increase STR by 5 (L1) to 25 (L40)<br>
<br>
<br>
Lodizal Shell Boots <br>
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM  <br>
AC: +14 Str: +7 HP: +20  <br>
Effect: Turtle Skin:  Increase AC by 10<br>
<br>
So, I will gain 1ac by switching to Cobalt, but loose 20hp and 7 str (can't use the cobalt effect yet).  I think I am going to stay with the lodi boots, much better IMHO. <br>
<br>
I'd like to get the sheild, but I'm Vahl Shir, so can't wear it, I belive, only lrg race that can is Iksar. <br>
<br>
Tried for frosty, but too expensive, will looking in getting another lammy or a Defiance if I still have the cash for them.  <br>
<br>
Frosty costs arouund 6-7k latley, but the SoEE only costs about 700pp on the rathe, figured it was a good deal.  Trying to work up 1hb, have a blackjack and the IBC, the haste proc is nice when I can't get any other haste. <br>
<br>
Thanks for the suggestions, keep em coming.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=494369"><br>
Avenol Whiteflame, 31 Warrior</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=534768">Rezzinx Shadowsoul, 31 Cleric of Tunare</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
The Rathe<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crathsorgnawbone>Crathsor Gnawbone</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/28/02 8:36:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Introduction, and a question.</span><hr size=1> Just posting to point out that you'd gain a little more than 1 AC from Cobalt Boots.  The Lodizal's 10 AC bonus is exactly that - 10 AC.  When you gain 11 raw AC from the Cobalt you will actually pick up around 16 AC total, and you don't have to remember to click it.<br>
<br>
CG <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=knomekabobb>KnomeKabobb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/28/02 12:09:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Introduction, and a question.</span><hr size=1> At level 31 I'd rather have the 7str and 20hp than the 5 or so raw AC you'd get from Cobalt.  Sell/trade them and get Cobalt at 46 though, that's when they'll really come in handy. <p>[55 Myrmidon]<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=475259">Bulky Behemoth</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->(Troll)<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.savagearms.org">&lt;Savage Arms&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wubaogoldenarmz>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 353<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/28/02 4:50:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   lol</span><hr size=1> At level 31, the 5 raw AC is actually much more useful than the 20 hit points.<br>
<br>
If 1 AC = 6hp, then 5 AC = 30 hit points.<br>
<br>
If 1 AC = 4hp, then 5 AC = 20 hit points.<br>
<br>
Here's the thing though, at level 31, that 5 AC may put you closer to an AC cap that will actually see mitigation benefits.<br>
<br>
If this were a level 60 toon, and you were sitting at 1245 AC and trying to decide, odds are the 20 hit points would server you better.<br>
<br>
But at level 31, the benefits from the AC may actually be much more worthwhile.<br>
<br>
-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bingor>Bingor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/29/02 6:02:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4733.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~timharron/Bingor.jpg width=140 heighth=160></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: lol</span><hr size=1> AC &gt; all, is still true for lower levels.<br>
<br>
/Bing <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52906">Marshall Bingor</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
